{"key":"processedPost-9552189","value":{"id":9552189,"first":9551239,"last":9557106,"when":1231199090,"utime":"01/06/09 01:44 AM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />so what would cause massive levels of condensation in my tubs and fruiting chambers when i only have a temperature differential of about 3 degrees ??? </blockquote><br />Easy.&nbsp; As I said above, if there's a temperature differential AND above zero humidity, condensation will form.&nbsp; If the surface of the tub causes the air right against it to be cooled to the dewpoint, condensation will be formed, and this condensation is formed from moisture that used to be humidity in the air.&nbsp; Thus, the air is now not as humid as it was before."}}